  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Scheduled infrainguinal (femoropopliteal or infrapopliteal or both) angioplasty and/or
             stenting.

          -  Surgical or endovascular treatment of Inflow iliac artery significant stenosis if
             deemed necessary.

          -  Symptomatic severe intermittent claudication (Rutherford-Becker 3) or critical limb
             ischemia (Rutherford-Becker 4-6).

          -  Informed consent signed

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any contraindication to aspirin or cilostazol intake

          -  No pedal arch outflow

          -  Sole iliac artery treatment

          -  Standard contraindications to angioplasty

          -  Acute or sub-acute limb ischemia
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
